value.0: Blue milk, sometimes known as Bantha milk is a blue-colored liquid produced by a female bantha's mammary glands. It can be found on most planets across the galaxy. The milk is well known for being very rich and  refreshing, its opaque coloring suggesting that it is also sweet. The milk is also used to make a variety of yogurt, ice cream, and cheese. Its ubiquity inspired the military phrase blue milk run.
